net.sf.mmm.util.lang.api

Class Password

  • java.lang.Object
    • net.sf.mmm.util.lang.api.AbstractDatatype
      • net.sf.mmm.util.lang.api.AbstractSimpleDatatypeBase<V>
        • net.sf.mmm.util.lang.api.AbstractSimpleDatatype<String>
          • net.sf.mmm.util.lang.api.Password
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    Serializable, AttributeReadValue<String>, Security, Datatype, SimpleDatatype<String>

    public class Password
extends AbstractSimpleDatatype<String>
implements Security
    This is the Datatype used to store a simple password as String. Its string representation is a fixed String (********) in order to prevent accidental logging or other spreading of passwords. The actually get the password as String use AbstractSimpleDatatype.getValue().
    Since:
    6.0.0
    Author:
    Joerg Hohwiller (hohwille at users.sourceforge.net)
    See Also:

    • Method Detail

      • toString

        public String toString()
        Description copied from interface: Datatype
        Returns the official String representation of this Datatype. While the general contract of Object.toString() is very weak and mainly used for debugging, the contract here is very strong. The returned String has to be suitable for end-users and official output to any kind of sink.
        ATTENTION:
        This method is not supposed to do internationalization (I18N). See NlsMessage for this purpose and implement NlsObject if you want to support I18N/L10N.
        Specified by:
        toString in interface Datatype
        Overrides:
        toString in class AbstractSimpleDatatypeBase<String>
        Returns:
        the official String representation to display the value of this Datatype.
